caption: This spot provides fantastic service as well as yummy meals. The best spot in the city. The drinks and food served quick and the rates were economical. Recommended.
This place is excellent! Reasonable pricing, large portions and the staff members are constantly super friendly.

The guy running the and making the food is very friendly and personable. He recognizes his repeat customers and will make you an order of whatever you want. Huge portions are great prices. Vegan and vegetarian options are no problem. Great place for a healthy and delicious lunch.

The food is fine, but the owner (I assume the guy making the food is the owner) will put hot sauce on everything you buy no matter how much you beg him not to. I'm sick of him screwing up my order and won't be going back.

This restaurant is my number one place.  Of all restaurants I know I like it most. I always suggests to my friends to go to visit this place. when  I want to go to a proper supper, this place comes straightaway to my head. best and all sorts of  food and a rich cuisine.professional crew, and nice ambience. Not less important, the tariff is honest. I recommend this place with pleasure.
This place has very good and authentic food, one of my personal favorites around the city.
A top place for tasty turkish food. the staff was very friendly and kind. this place has a nice feel to it.

Little hole in the wall on Broad Street with incredibly authentic & fresh food! Take your lunch to-go, or ask them about the indoor seating next door. Great vegetarian options- falafel salad, mediterranean wraps, hummus etc. The owner & cashier both are amazingly KIND. If you find yourself in downtown Atlanta, i would highly suggest making a trip to Ali Baba for lunch.
Excellent Mediterranean food. The portions were plentiful and the food was really solid. This is the best Mediterranean I've had in Burbank.
Nice place for Turkish food. visited at eight, it was not full. the bill was average for the menu.
turkish food, yeah, super good. Came in on a Weds. Prices were decent.
Good service good food
Outstanding scene for quality Turkish food. I'll return with my relatives. Prices were good for how much you get.
turkish food, so delicious. Great location to meet with friends. The service here is friendly. This place has an awesome feel to it. I can see why they have a lot of positive reviews.
One of my fav locations for Turkish food. A favorite evening place of mine. Looking forward to a return visit. The prices are good for what you get. Atmosphere and food reminds me of Virginia Beach.
Very delicious
Super tasty!
Super
Best meal and service I have ever seen! Love it!
I have been there once while in Atlanta. OMG so delicious food and exceptional service! Thank you!
Very delicious foods. I love it.😍
The best mediterranean food everything is fresh and hot thank u 👍
A certain staff member made me feel sub human. I would not eat here if you paid me.
Worst experience ever, staff was extremely pff putting. Do not eat here.
turkish food and the scene here is super good. Food was so appetizing.
This place is worth a try. They serve large portions for reasonable rates. Consistently well kept and with excellent atmosphere. Will come visit again.

I celebrated my PhD earlier this evening in this great restaurant. I am glad to say that we enjoyed a fantastic evening and the venue was evidently one of the reasons for the fruitful event. The stuff  helped in a pleasant manner, the meals were yummy and my friends were very  thrilled. We shall surely visit again for more events. thanks very much.
For my money, best falafel in town. Always speedy service. I’m never disappointed.
This spot knows how to please their clients. Consistently with a very nice mindset. The food is affordably priced, always fresh and neat.
I stopped in here while on a layover in downtown Atlanta. The lamb gyro was wonderful. Thank you for being open during the pandemic.
This place obviously knows how to treat their clients. Constantly with a friendly attitude. The food is affordably priced, constantly flavorful and clean.

It was my first time trying and I must say food was great for the price! Staff went above and beyond letting me try new things and very accommodating! Very nice and helped me order in my native language which made the experience so much better! When they noticed I brought my dog and we were eating outside they even brought my dog some meat and water. I’ve never met staff that cares about their customers as much as Ali Baba Mediterranean in downtown.  If I could give 10 stars I would! I will be a returning customer and is now on my top recommended list.
FRESH quality food! I loved my lunch from beginning to end

I admire this spot! They offer excellent food, their menu is decent, The cook in that restaurant is a real authority in the kitchen, I love very much trying all their dishes. The dishes are always good, the attitude towards the visitors  is efficient. I frequently visit this place and I not even once was discontended. I recommend it to all.

This is a great place for a healthy, filling and cheap lunch. It is bar none my favorite place to eat lunch while in campus. For about $9 you get a rice or salad with chicken or lamb, a side, pita, and a drink. I always pick a chicken salad with hummus for a healthy meal that satisfies me all day. The people that run Ali Baba's are very nice and courteous, and sometimes they throw in a little extra food for you to try.

From the moment  you come to that place  the waiters give you a comfortable feeling. Very friendly team, it is a lovely place to  enjoy with buddies or with your date. delicious  cuisine, experienced  chef, honest  pay and attentive  service. Highly recommended.
They have great gyros, always fresh and well seasoned meat. They usually have a special that will feed you twice.
Very flavorful food from a very likeable guy! He's been there a long time. A local staple for the lunch crowd. Won't be disappointed!
I tried this spot already with my friend and I am obsessed since then. I enjoy the awesome character and delicious food and beverages. Great work.
Favorite Gyro place on GSU campus. Located in a tiny space off of Luckie Street.
Exceptional food, super nice staff members, regularly great atmosphere. They charge fair rates and the food quality is excellent. Fantastic work.

Actually I was next door at the pizza place for my fave spinach and anchovies  pizza. Ali Baba’s is okay, too. Interesting place Broad Street in downtown Atlanta. Cool places to have a quick bite. Ali Baba’s falafel used to be the bomb. Hope they’re still going strong.

I work upstairs in the Healey Building from this restaurant and frequent it often. Great fresh food, the owner and employees are always accommodating to special requests, plus it is delicious, quick, healthy and a great value for the price. I always have enough leftovers for a 2nd meal!
Best falafel in Atlanta! The falafel sandwich is full of veggies and falafel  and so satisfying.

I went today and got a gyro salad plate for me and a gyro wrap (it was called a “super” something...) for my husband. The staff were so kind and engaging and helped me decide what to order. They helped me figure out what each thing was and how to pick items best for me. The food was really tasty and very different for me to experience. I liked eating here and trying something new! Plus, the kind man preparing the food even gave me an extra sample of a side so that I could try a new item. Very kind of him! I appreciated it and will certainly go back.
It's super delicious! They have great falafel, and the staff is very kind. Definitely worth the trip for anyone who has doubts.
Great hole in the wall option on Broad. Good Med flavors. Salad is great. Chicken and rice is great. Hummus and falafef great. Friendly people. Know
I walked passed this place a few times. The location is very small, blink and you will miss it. I ate here two days in a row. Enjoyed my salads very much.
Really friendly service.  Authentic food that was delicious. Affordable prices.  Some seating outside but additional seating inside downstairs.  I would recommend checking it out
Great people and food quality. The serving a good size and it tastes amazing. Good gyro and greek salad.
Constantly Good
Amazing and authentic!
The food is awesome so is the owner who treats customer with respect and care. Highly recommended.
turkish food, yeah, super yummy. One of the best spots in the area. Looking forward to coming back with my relatives.

Don't overlook this place. Tiny stall and a little rough looking, but this place will get you some delicious food quickly and with friendly service. I was getting it to go, but they pointed out there's indoor seating in the building they butt up against which resolves the only issue I'd have with the place.
Wonderful food!
One of my preferred locations for tasty Turkish food. the staff was helpful and kind. the bill was well within reason for the quality.
Can't remember what I had. I'd been eating out frequently.  I do remember, it is worth going again.
SAYS BEST FALAFEL IN TOWN BUT IT IS THE WORST FALAFEL IN TOWN THE FALAFEL LITERALLY TASTE LIKE DOUGH!!! Throw in lettuce, tomato,  mix veggies and you have your wrap.
Best Falafel Everrrrrr! Customer service is great too. They’re very nice. I will be a frequent customer
Great food excellent customer service
Give it a try!
Good food and hospitality. Prices reasonable.
I love the Mediterranean platter!!! Best Falafel ive ever had!!

Always enjoy the Mediterranean wrap from this place but dealing with the lady behind the register is enough to stop me from going here unless I’m in a hurry. She is curt, unhelpful, and generally unpleasant, which is why I’ve only ever ordered one item off the menu—I’m too anxious to ask questions about other menu items because I excpect a rude and scornful response (which I’ve seen her deliver to other customers countless times). If you’ve got an itch for Mediterranean food in Downtown Atlanta, I recommend making the short walk over to Baraka Shawarma instead.

Don't let this hole in the wall foo. you.  The food is delicious.  My go to item is the gyro salad.  It's got a ton of veggies:  tomatoes, cucumber, peppers, olives, onions and of course the meat.  And the falafel is delish!

If you enjoy tasteless and oily meat then this is the place.   In all my  years eating Gyros( Lamb or Chicken) in NYC never...ever have they been flavorless or oily....not even from the street carts/vendors..Lol!!  Straight BASURA ( garbage/trash). When you know better..you eat better!! # FACTS

Greek salad with lamb is my favorite, and such a good price. Loaded with meat and veggies, it'll fill you up for the day. So much parsley tops off the flavor explosion in this salad. Tiny spot for ordering, but you can eat either at a table in the sidewalk or in the area downstairs.
Really bland gyro, no taste. I got the chicken gyro and I could see the grease. Had to throw it away after two bites. Plenty of better places to get gyro than here, I wouldn’t recommend.
Great med food, fast, cheap, legit.   Don't pass this up. #travelformortals
Food is not good
It's ok

This is an excellent facility with outside tables and chairs to view the scenery. They have an array of Turkish foods and desserts that melt in your mouth. If you like international food's I suggest you go check this eatery out.  You will be Surprised!!! Thank you Fevzi Karabulut who's the owner and his delightful staff, especially the cashier. Peace, Love and Joy to you all.
One of the better doners I've had state side. My only disappointment?  No Frites.

This is my favorite spot on Broad. I'M A Georgia State University employee and I'm calling out to you Panthers....eat HERE. It's healthy...tasty and you can't beat the great service. Shouts out to their main Cashier (the brunette lady) she completely understands Customer retention. I'll be back 100%
So good! Will definitely be back!
Best falafel wraps downtown! They also have excellent vegan samosas.
Wonderful meal at a great price. The salad was great as well as the hummus.
Great street food. Good tzatziki sauce. Good sandwiches and very reasonable pricing. They offer student discounts too. No indoor seating.
I ate all my food before I got to take a pic. Trust me when I say it's good. I sat by the window, best seat to people watch. Check the place out!

I love Ali Baba's for a quick lunch on the go at a reasonable price. I always get the Gyro + Mediterranean Salad combo for $7. It's filling, delicious, cheap, and comes prepackaged in a styrofoam to go container. The super gyro is more meat and sauce, which makes it a bit harder to eat. The drinks are in a separate storefront. They offer discounts for GSU students. There isn't a place to sit down here, it's more of a permanent stand than a restaurant. The park is barely a block away, and they have lots of seating there, so I recommend that.
The place is scary, the service rough, but it taste good :)
GSU student discount 10%

Ali baba is a GREAT place for lunch, EVERYDAY. The food here is amazing and inexpensive as well. AND, they give you a LOT of food. A little on the greasy side, but not enough to keep me away! Everyone I've recommended this place too says more or less the same. Everyone should try it.
Great hole-in-the-wall Mediterranean restaurant. Delicious lamb gyro! But if you are looking for atmosphere and excellent service, go elsewhere.

When I approached the cashier with a question, no hi, hello, nothing. She continued to play on her phone, barely answered my question. Very rude & unconcerned.I went next door to the pizza joint and received  excellent customer service. I will never go there again. I assumed. because the cook didn't speak English that the establishment would be friendly to people of color! WRONG!!!!!!!!
I ordered shawarma but i didn't like it. It was full of spices.
I go here A LOT. The gyro is the best in Atlanta.

Tiny place. Split by another entrance, but you can get great quality very quickly here. Try the falafal! I've had the falafal, gyros, and a couple of other items. All very good. Expect to haul it off to eat it. Some outdoor seating under the trees nearby. Soda machine/drinks are not in the space in which you order!

RUDE customer service. I was the only person inside the restaurant (so there was no line/wait) and asked the lady behind the counter questions about prices and the menu. She seemed bothered by my asking questions and gave me attitude. She called me "sweetie" and condescendingly said "I think you're confused". It was exactly like interacting with a bully. Needless to say I did not lunch with them, and will never step foot at Ali Babas again.
Best Shawrma
This place is delicious and the people are nice.  I think they've given me extra sides many times for just being friendly and smiling.  Great food and a guilt free lunch with lots of veggie options!
The hunnus here is awesome. The men that do the cooking are also very nice. But the lady who runs the register is NOT! She is very unwelcoming & rude. I try to avoid going there when shes there.
Really good meat and vegi options at an ultra conveiniant location. The prices are reasonable, I could go everyday.
It is the best Mediterranean restaurant in Atlanta.  It beats the fancy upscale restaurants in term of taste.  The falafels taste better than the ones at other Mediterranean restaurants.

The food has always been great when I went there. The tiny store is always busy, with a line that occasionally goes half-way down Broad Street, which is my only complaint. Overall, it is a well priced, worthwhile experience that I will continue to enjoy on my afternoon walks.

My girlfriend and I got lunch at Ali-baba's today. I had the Falafel salad and she had the lunch special with chicken (meat over rice w/ two sides). The serving size to price ratio is good; just under $8 for a very filling lunch. The quality of my salad was mehhh. The falafel was smothered in yogurt and hot sauce to the point that I felt like I was eating a buffalo chicken salad. But, more notably, my girlfriend got food poisoning from the chicken.  I gotta believe that this place has something to offer based on all the good reviews it has. I'd say check it out if you're on GSU campus and need a filling lunch, just hold off on the sauce if you want to taste the food and stay away from the chicken.

Today makes my second visit here. I ordered the gyro yesterday and it was so good that I decided to come back today. The lady at the front had the most stank, unappealing attitude I've ever encountered. I asked for the falafel to be my side, but what they put in the box didn't look the same. I asked her if it came with what I asked and I was met with belligerence. The experience was so unpleasant that I'm probably never going back again. It's unfortunate cause the food is really good and decently priced. I'll come back though if she's not there...

The best gyro anywhere. We have had gyros in Turkey, and all over the USA but by golly this is the best Gyro. The owner's Dad actually is a chef in Istanbul and has a chain of restaurants there employing 300.  So it was no surprise for us that every item on Ali Baba's menu that we tasted here on Broad street; was very palatable, very delicious, perfectly cooked and well seasoned.  We tried the Bakalwa for desert. Sinfully delicious. Like all other Bakalwas this one was not dripping or soaked in honey. The amount was just perfect.  Honestly, if you haven't eaten Gyro, falafal or for that matter; if you haven't  eaten at Ali Baba Cafe you have no idea what true good Turkish food tastes like.  I have spent two weeks in Turkey eating at authentic restaurants and even here in Atlanta at Turkish festivals and other so called authentic Turkish and Greek outfits. This is a fast food style cafe and seating is on the sidewalk.  All I can say is get down to 60 Broad Street, Atlanta GA. You will be  back.
Literally crave the Mediterranean wrap. Simply amazing!
This is a hole in the wall, but I like the vegetarian wrap.
The best gyros in Atlanta.

I have been to Mediterranean restaurants all over the country.   It is one of my favorite foods.  I typically order a falafel sandwich.   The falafel part of the sandwich was luke warm or cold.  It was tasty.   But they just put in a small piece.  I would have preferred a slightly larger portion.  But it is very lazy for the restaurant not to warm it up.   The pita was good and the fixins inside were good.  I also got grape leaves.  They were terrible.  Very mushy and also too cold.   I also got a samosa.   That was also cold.  They said they could heat it up but in a microwave.   It is 2014, how can a classy place heat things up in a device that ruins food.  I ate it cold and it was pretty good.  I think if this place had their ingredients at the right temperature they would be much better off.  So if you want cold/luke warm food this is your spot.

THIS PLACE DOES NOT HAVE OPEN HOURS POSTED. I am here thirty minutes after noon and it is closed.  This is the second place in Atlanta that failed my family. We are glad that the Naan Stop neighboring restaurant serves some halaal.
It's closed
My favorite place to eat for lunch downtown. The food is amazing. The guy with the Michigan hat at the front is very nice. I try to eat here every week. If you get a chance try the spanakopita.
Consistently the best in town. I love the fact that they're only a block away from where I work, which makes them great for lunch.
